                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/1349: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Warren</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-05-31T11:00:00+09:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 31, 1922—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 31—9:16 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>90. Foreign Office has given me official statement that Government has decided
                    speedily to withdraw Japanese troops from Hankow. Statement says action is based
                    on policy of respecting the integrity and sovereignty of China and is in keeping
                    with resolutions adopted by Washington Conference.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Warren</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
